text: Great God, I ask for no meaner pelf%% Than that I may not disappoint myself,
Than that I may not disappoint myself, That in my action I may soar as high
That in my action I may soar as high%% As I can now discern with this clear eye.
As I can now discern with this clear eye. And next in value, which thy kindness lends,
And next in value, which thy kindness lends, That I may greatly disappoint my friends,
That I may greatly disappoint my friends, Howe'er they think or hope that it may be,
Howe'er they think or hope that it may be, They may not dream how thou'st distinguished me.
They may not dream how thou'st distinguished me. That my weak hand may equal my firm faith
That my weak hand may equal my firm faith%% And my life practice what my tongue saith
And my life practice what my tongue saith%% That my low conduct may not show
That my low conduct may not show%% Nor my relenting lines
Nor my relenting lines%% That I thy purpose did not know
That I thy purpose did not know%% Or overrated thy designs.
